      <hedline>
        <hl1>Asian Cuisines Understood Salt</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kasha Loha-Unchit letter on salt in desserts (Aug 30 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Salt in desserts? Combining savory and sweet? Hardly novel or innovative. The Chinese and Southeast Asians have been doing it for a long time. Take for instance a salted duck-egg yolk in a sweet moon cake, salty-sweet coconut cream dribbled over sticky rice and served with lusciously sweet mangos, or fried onions and garlic sprinkled over a creamy rich and sweet coconut egg custard. Glad to hear Western chefs are finally catching on.</p>
        <p>KASMA LOHA-UNCHIT  Oakland, Calif.</p>
      </block>
